Sass Installation Log

Goal: Install the sass command-line compiler using npm (Node Package Manager) for a specific version.

Prerequisites: Node.js and npm must be installed on the system.

Steps Taken:

Open Terminal/Command Prompt: Opened the command-line interface (Terminal on macOS/Linux or Command Prompt/PowerShell on Windows).

Execute Installation Command: Ran the following command to install the sass package globally on the system and pin it to version 3.7.4:

npm install -g sass@3.7.4


Verification: To confirm the installation and version, the following command can be executed:

sass --version


(The output should indicate the successful installation of Sass version 3.7.4.)